@Arkre: In most languages, variable shadowing are variables in inner scope shadowing ones in outer scope.
But Rust allows shadowing and shadowned variables in the same scope.
This may be confusing. 

```rust
fn main() {
    let x = 1;
    // N lines later...
    println!("x is {}", x);
    // N lines later...
    let x = 1.0;
    // N lines later...
    println!("x is {}", x);
}
```
